#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.35"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.35:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.35:0.2"
msgid "4. Sīsapāvanavagga"
msgstr "4. In a Rosewood Forest"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn56.35:0.3"
msgid "35. Sattisatasutta"
msgstr "35. A Hundred Spears"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.441"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.35:1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso vassasatāyuko vassasatajīvī."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, suppose there was a man with a lifespan of a hundred years."

msgctxt "sn56.35:1.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "And someone might say to him:"

msgctxt "sn56.35:1.3"
msgid ""
"‘ehambho purisa, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ taṃ sattisatena hanissanti, "
"majjhanhikasamayaṃ sattisatena hanissanti, sāyanhasamayaṃ sattisatena "
"hanissanti."
msgstr ""
"‘Come now, my good man, they’ll strike you with a hundred spears in the "
"morning, at midday, and in the late afternoon."

msgctxt "sn56.35:1.4"
msgid ""
"So kho tvaṃ, ambho purisa, divase divase tīhi tīhi sattisatehi haññamāno "
"vassasatāyuko vassasatajīvī vassasatassa accayena anabhisametāni cattāri "
"ariyasaccāni abhisamessasī’ti."
msgstr ""
"And you’ll live for a hundred years being struck with three hundred spears "
"every day. But when a hundred years have passed, you will comprehend the "
"four noble truths for the first time.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.35:2.1"
msgid "Atthavasikena, bhikkhave, kulaputtena alaṃ upagantuṃ."
msgstr ""
"For an earnest and respectable person this is sufficient reason to submit."

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.3"
msgid "Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro;"
msgstr "Transmigration has no known beginning."

#. VAR: asippahārānaṃ usuppahārānaṃ pharasuppahārānaṃ → asippahārānaṃ (sī1), asipahārānam parasupahārānaṃ (pā1), asippahārānaṃ pharasuppahārānaṃ (ka-ma)
msgctxt "sn56.35:2.4"
msgid ""
"pubbā koṭi nappaññāyati sattippahārānaṃ asippahārānaṃ usuppahārānaṃ "
"pharasuppahārānaṃ."
msgstr "No first point is found of blows by spears, swords, arrows, and axes."

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.5"
msgid "Evañcetaṃ, bhikkhave, assa."
msgstr "Now this may be so."

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.6"
msgid ""
"Na kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, saha dukkhena, saha domanassena catunnaṃ "
"ariyasaccānaṃ abhisamayaṃ vadāmi;"
msgstr ""
"But the comprehension of the four noble truths doesn’t come with pain or "
"sadness, I say."

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.7"
msgid ""
"api cāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sahāva sukhena, sahāva somanassena catunnaṃ "
"ariyasaccānaṃ abhisamayaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"Rather, the comprehension of the four noble truths comes only with pleasure "
"and happiness, I say."

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.8"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.9"
msgid ""
"Dukkhassa ariyasaccassa … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya "
"ariyasaccassa."
msgstr "The noble truths of suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.35:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.35:3.2"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
